content: The Network+ version of this app helped me pass with an 833. Didn't hesitate to buy the Security+ app to help with my next certification. I'm using this along with Darril Gibson's book.

Great questions, average app. Works well, although I see repeat questions a lot, which some people may like. The interface is a bit dated. I wish there were more features to show you your progress in specific areas, beyond the "proficiency" score. Overall, I think this is a useful app.
Great study tool helped me pass the 501

This definitely helped me study and pass. Some of the questions were very similar to what i experienced on the exam. I would recommend this as a supplementary study aid for when you're on the go and have a moment for a quick refresher quiz.

This app has great content that goes hand and hand with the Sec+ Book. If you read the book by Darril Gibson and practice the questions in this app you should pass the test on the first try. Good Luck All!!
Will you guys have 601 available soon please?
This is great. Will this be updated to 601 when it comes out?

Questions are great and you can focus on particular objectives that you're weak in. The explanations are very helpful as well. As for the issues with text being cut off, turn your device into landscape mode and it will display the rest of the text.

This is a good app to get started into the sec+ experience. I will say that a lot of questions, particularly the answer explanations are unfinished. I see the right answer but I would like to know why the other answers are wrong to get a better understanding of the objectives. Needs an overhaul of the answer explanations.
App is a great supplement, can give questions around a topic and has explanations for wrong answers.
I passed first try and thanks to this app I was able to solidify my weak domains and concepts. Thanks!
Good app. Used it to review terminology wherever I had to wait in line or sit outside. I didn't experience any crashes.
This was a great resource, just passed my test today and the flash cards this app provides helped me fill the gaps in knowledge. Would recommend 100%
Excellent way to go forward!
The app keeps crashing so I cant even complete the test. I would like a full refund as this is a waste of my money.

Great app, though some of the questions get cut off and the answer choices cover it from time to time. 9 times out of 10 you can figure it out, but not sure if it's just my phone or if others have the same issue. Either way, still a fantastic app.
It's a great tool and easy to use. The mix of flash cards and exam questions is beneficial as well. The only issue I have is the app always crashes at flashcard 37 in every category.
It keeps crashing/app suddenly closes by itself all the time.
With the exception of the visual simulation in the actual test, this app does a great job of getting your head around the right content.
I was recommended this app by someone who recently passed the test and I am astounded by the volume of questions and coherent explanations.

Very good review for before the test. Some of the answers dont make much sense, but it's rare to come across. I like how it tells you which categories to improve on, so that you can study on exactly what you need! Very simplistic design for quick tests and access. I definitely recommend if going for Security+
This is a great app and compliments Darril Gibson book on Security+. I used this and the book and was able to pass the test.
Pretty pricey but it is helpful for quick refreshers

Fantastic questions but buggy. Multiple times it marks questions wrong where I picked the right answer. I won't do tests above 10 questions on this app because I want to make sure I memorize my answers when it grades me so I can check. Also I would love some statistics to see where I need to focus studying. I find the pocket prep app better with more features but this one has better questions... If you put these questions into the pocket prep app it would be the perfect study guide
Helps a little. App material is not enough to pass tough. Study the book and other practice exams with more realistic exam questions. It will help more...
Great app! Has worked amazing while adding another level of confidence before I take the Sec+ Exam.

The app is basically a lazy design with all the questions copy and pasted from the book, everything single question. While it's convenient to have all the questions handy, the price point can't be justified, especially if the app can't remember that you already started a test when you restart the app.

I will admit that the practice test questions were nothing like the actual questions on the Pearson Vue test but they were and teaching me how to learn a thought process. plus when you got the answer wrong it explained to you why it was wrong and showed you the right answer and explained why it was the right answer. Also, it may be more importantly, the acronyms dictionary is what really helped me the most in passing my CompTIA Security+ exam. Acronyms help with the questions on the test.
I used this app after studying a textbook. It definitely helped me pass.

The app is great but do I really need to purchase this app again to use it on a new phone?? Surely not? Edit: Thank you - just took a few days to sync. It is now showing as " Purchased" on the new device.
replyContent: No, you don't have to buy again for another device, as long as you use the same google play account. See https://support.google.com/googleplay/answer/113410?co=GENIE.Platform%3DAndroid&hl=en

content: Amazing

Let us save where we left off please! It gets really annoying to start over and over and over and over from the beggining again and again and again.
replyContent: Hi Mark, The questions/flashcards do not start from the beginning. They are displayed in random order every time. But I can understand why this could be frustrating. We will add this feature soon. Please send me an email at support@learnzapp.com.

content: Used the older version and it was great for learning. They released this new version which is good but unfortunately doesn't save where you left off. So if you do 10 questions, leave and come back to studying you have start from the beginning. Also there is a lot of empty space at the bottom of the questions and answers. Other than that it's a great learning app. Edit: Still no save where you left off after update.
replyContent: Hi, The questions are displayed in random order every time. You do not have to start from the beginning. But I understand why this could be annoying. We will add this feature soon. Please send an email at support@learnzapp.com for more details.

I passed with this helpful app!!!
perfect for preparing for the exam. very easy interface with plenty of practice questions and good explanations in the answers. well worth the money

Took my exam (501) today and passed! Thanks mostly to this app! Studied this app occasionally for 6 weeks. Then studied this app a couple hours a day for 2 more weeks. Only thing this app lacks is "scenarios". Also don't forget to Study the acronyms (this app has those too). Studied this app 2 months. Passed!
studied the 501 section and just took the exam. i failed. there were maybe 5 questions on this app that i saw on the actual exam. what a waste of money.
Great way to learn all the content but don't rely only on this app. Questions are trickier on the exam.

Awesome app
This app was critical in my preparation for the exam. Highly recommend.

Great study material that can be used as the foundation for your test prep. I passed well over the minimum while using this for the majority of my studying. The recommended YouTube videos made my eyes glaze over and I didn't have time to read one of the books front to back. Instead I used this app and found a dump for the simulations. Everyone learns differently though, I only suggest whatever method you use that you make sure you are comprehending what the answer is and not just memorizing.

I used this app for 2 weeks and was able to pass the Security+ exam. I did not use the text book that goes along with the app, however I definitely noticed a couple things missing after taking the test

Took security+ sy0-501 today and passed with a 784. Used this app for practice tests, watched all of professor messers videos, and did performance based questions on the Gibson website. This app definitely helped me out!

This app is well worth $8. Complex questions broken down by domain and practice test. Questions also provide detailed explanations to review. This app combined with reading a sec+ book got it done for me. Like all test questions tho, DO NOT just memorize them and think you'll pass. Still gotta read a book. Read a book.

I used a couple different paid and free apps to help me study for the exam (which I passed first try today) and, coupled with the book from the same author, this one I believe was the most beneficial. The interface is really simplistic and I feel it could use some extra features to help review and monitor your progress, but the questions were great, varied, and had the most detailed feedback that not only told you what the write answer was, but why the others were wrong. If you only have the money for one study app, I think this one is your best bet.

Passed today, this app was the best resource I had, and the style of 
questions closely emulated those of the exam. An excellent app.

Passed the 401 yesterday with this app and Comptia Cert Master; I used 
nothing else. This app was better than Cert Master because it tells you why 
an answer is correct AND why the incorrect answers are incorrect.

So this app has a lot of good information, that being said this shouldn't 
be your only study source. What this app does give you is a better 
understanding of how the questions on the test are worded/layered. I 
probably ran through at least 50 practice tests. Spend the money, it's 
worth it.

I passed my Security+ yesterday morning. I mostly used the book, this app, 
and few videos on pluralsight. Very good combination. I studied for about a 
month and a half. My advice would be to think of thinks in a situational 
way.

Passed the Security+ exam yesterday. I used a combination of materials 
including this app and CompTIA's Certmaster training. This app was by FAR 
more representative of the questions on the exam. If I had to do it again I 
would just use this app to study and skip the Certmaster stuff.

Today I passed the Security+ exam. I exclusively used this app to prepare 
for the test. All I did was review the flashcards for a little over a month 
when I had time. If I was sitting in a waiting room for 10 minutes, or 
eating lunch I'd flip through some. It was a very casual pace. I didn't 
really start buckling down until 3 weeks out from the exam. That was when I 
flipped my tactics and went exclusively for the questions and quizzes. I 
was able to easily identify where I was weak (which was the encryption 
module for me) and I focused there. To think, I nearly spent $400 for a 
community college prep course. Instead, I spent 8 dollars on this and 
passed.

Dont buy this. Waste of money....real test has weird questions full of 
stuff that don't even appear in the book. Dont buy this!!! Just google for 
question, look deep and you will find enough!

Great app, but WHO made the decision to switch between questions by 
swiping??? It makes it nearly impossible to scroll down through questions 
without flipping forward or back. They need to revise the code on this asap.

I passed my 501 with a 892 all thanks to this app. With a Bachelors Degree 
in Cyber security and this app, I was able to I knock the test out of the 
park

While none of the apps test questions are even close to the real test 
questions, if you study the explanations of not only the correct ones, but 
also I the incorrect ones, you should be able to learn enough to pass the 
test. I passed first try. I have been in it for several years though.

There's no better app for practice questions. If you can answer these 
questions you'll pass. I passed the exam on my 1st attempt using this as 
one of my study resources. Well worth the price

This is a great study guide app for sec+ I used mostly this and professor 
messer videos to study and I passed no problem. Comes with flash cards as 
well

I passed the 501 exam on my first try today, and this app helped me  get there.  It doesn't replace reading Gibson's textbook, but it's a useful portable resource.  Towards the end of my studies, I just kept doing practice tests on this app until I consistently scored in the 90s.  The flashcards are relevant and the practice test questions are in a style similar to the real thing.   Tl;dr: it was worth the money.

I used this app as my main study tool along with the GCGA website premium content. The questions are the same but online it has a few performance based scenarios.  I passed the SY0-501 today after about a month of studying. The test had a lot of scenarios not covered in the app but I feel the content greatly helped me understand the subjects. I recommend the app to anyone as a great suplemental study aid!

Passed my Security+ exam yesterday. The actual exam jas lot of tricky questions which basically test ur understanding thoroughly.This app along with the book is the right combination to prepare before the exam. Switched careers,  non IT background, used this app as supplement to other online sources,  took the exam and passed.  This app is a great help.  Recommend for anyone preparing for sec plus.
4 STARS * * * * There's no basic way to close the app after using it. Please find a way to fix this as I've paid for the FULL VERSION. 5 stars whenever this gets resolved. Good app other than that.
